<span id="freeTextContainer14008356741095345527">I was very pleased to be invited for an interview on Burl Barer&apos;s &apos;True Crime Uncensored&apos; programme on Outlaw Radio, broadcasting live from Los Angeles. You can hear the programme on a podcast by clicking this link: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://bit.ly/2QdsWaM'>https://bit.ly/2QdsWaM</a><br/><br/>My first book &quot;The Rotherham Trunk Murder&quot; was written after I uncovered a miscarriage of justice - a man hanged for a crime he did not commit.<br/><br/>My second book &quot;Edw</span>
  <span id="freeText14008356741095345527" style="display:none">I was very pleased to be invited for an interview on Burl Barer's 'True Crime Uncensored' programme on Outlaw Radio, broadcasting live from Los Angeles. You can hear the programme on a podcast by clicking this link: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://bit.ly/2QdsWaM">https://bit.ly/2QdsWaM</a><br /><br />My first book "The Rotherham Trunk Murder" was written after I uncovered a miscarriage of justice - a man hanged for a crime he did not commit.<br /><br />My second book "Edwin, Adelaide and George" tells the bizarre story of Adelaide Bartlett, her husband Edwin and her lover George. This Victorian murder mystery has puzzled everyone for over a hundred years, but having had access to the full transcript of Adelaide's 6 day trial at The Old Bailey I put forward a new theory to explain the mystery.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14008356741095345527" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

